    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey my realtor just mentioned something about an escrow account for the closing and i'm kinda confused. what exactly is escrow and why do i need it for the house purchase?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "An escrow account is a fund held by a third party, typically a title company or attorney, that holds money until certain conditions are met in a real estate transaction, such as the sale of a house. In the case of buying a house, an escrow account is used to hold funds for property taxes and insurance until the closing date. This ensures that these expenses are paid when due, but isn't paid upfront. It helps prevent financial hardship if the sale doesn't go through.",
      "source": "target",
