    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "okay that makes sense. so basically someone else is just holding onto the money so nobody gets ripped off? is there anything specific i should watch out for with the escrow agent or any common issues that pop up during that stage?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Until the closing, the escrow agent holds onto the down payment and earnest money until all conditions are met. It's a safety net to protect both parties. One common issue is miscommunication or discrepancies in paperwork, so it's crucial to review all documents carefully and promptly address any concerns with the escrow agent or your realtor. It's also important to select a reputable escrow agent with a good track record and license.",
      "source": "target",
